The paper proposes a new approach for compressing deep neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision research (cs.LG, cs.CV). The proposed method involves iterative low-rank factorization and fine-tuning, which are techniques commonly used in optimization and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.NE). The paper also discusses the compression rate and accuracy of the method, which are important metrics in data compression and machine learning (cs.DS).
